PURPOSES (§ 11-3302)
    The StE District is intended to provide for the development of this site with aix of uses, achieved through the adaptive reuse of existing buildings as wells new construction.
    The StE District is intended to provide for a broad mix of uses, includingesidential, commercial, hospitality, educational, and civic uses consistentith the Master Plan, with a target of approximately four million two hundredhousand (4,200,000) square
      feet of development, exclusive of the StE-2, StE-18,nd StE-19 subdistricts and specified above-grade parking.
    The purposes of the StE District are to:
    Improve community connectivity and access to and through the campus;
    Enhance the unique and historic identity of the campus;
    Reinvigorate the campus as an important neighborhood center;
    Preserve and adaptively reuse the historic resources;
    Embody the District’s design and sustainability goals;
    Create a safe public realm and enhanced pedestrian experience;
    Enhance multi-modal transportation networks;
    Support wider economic development initiatives; and
    Ensure a parking supply that meets the needs of the St Elizabeths site whileinimizing impacts on surrounding neighborhoods and incurring acceptable impactsn the surrounding road network.
    Land Use and Urban Design principles for the StE District include:
    Create a safe environment by providing for a mix of uses and open spaces thatre capable of being programmed to ensure vitality and social activity;
    Create a desirable development opportunity by providing for flexibility in usesnd appropriate building heights and densities;
    Provide street-activating uses such as retail on the ground floor of buildingslong designated public streets;
    Recognize the unique and historic characteristics of the site and provide forhe appropriate reuse of the historic buildings and new development that willespect the site’s historic nature;
    Design and site new development sensitively to preserve existing gateways,istas, and campus landmarks;
    Create focal points to help establish a unique sense of place and orientation;
    Provide for significant open space, including community parks, plazas, andatural open space on the site;
    Provide for the preservation of the existing ravine within subdistrict StE-19 ints current, natural state; and
    Promote the use of best practice environmental and stormwater management design.
